Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.55,0:00:24.08,Default,,0,0,0,,[music]\N[music]
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.08,0:00:31.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Here\Nhe [music]
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.44,0:00:46.16,Default,,0,0,0,,>> [music]\N[music]
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.16,0:00:50.64,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Now the rate of happiness this is a\Nlittle bit different way of doing it. Uh
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.64,0:00:55.52,Default,,0,0,0,,the the log of the uh calibrated level\Nof consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.52,0:01:00.16,Default,,0,0,0,,what is the percent of happiness?\NSo you see that happiness is a
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.16,0:01:04.79,Default,,0,0,0,,consequence of level of consciousness\Nnot a consequence of what you own in the
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.79,0:01:11.76,Default,,0,0,0,,world or what titles you have or whether\Nyou're pretty or famous. Uh if you uh
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.76,0:01:17.75,Default,,0,0,0,,are here at 250 which is comfortable the\Nchances are about 60% 60% of people
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.75,0:01:22.56,Default,,0,0,0,,there are going to be happy. So the way\Nto achieve happiness is not through out
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.56,0:01:29.75,Default,,0,0,0,,there but in here. You can't achieve\Nhappiness by acquisition. You can only
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.75,0:01:34.88,Default,,0,0,0,,achieve it through advancing your level\Nof consciousness. You see that people at
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.88,0:01:39.92,Default,,0,0,0,,the bottom their rate of happiness is\Nzero. The rate of happiness down here
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.92,0:01:47.20,Default,,0,0,0,,below consciousness level. So 200 again\Nis the critical line. Above 200 55% of
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.20,0:01:54.32,Default,,0,0,0,,the people are happy. The minute you go\Nbelow the line it drops to 22%.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.32,0:01:58.39,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no way to make these people\Nhappy.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.39,0:02:03.68,Default,,0,0,0,,They will say that\Nthere's no way and nothing you can do
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.68,0:02:10.72,Default,,0,0,0,,that will make people who calibrate\Nbelow 200 happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.72,0:02:14.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing.\NGive up your life. Give up your
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.48,0:02:17.52,Default,,0,0,0,,property. Turn over your country. Turn\Nover your wife. Turn over your children.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.52,0:02:22.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Enslave everybody and you will not make\Nthem happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.79,0:02:25.52,Default,,0,0,0,,[laughter]\Nhere. I thought we were going to make
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.52,0:02:32.31,Default,,0,0,0,,thy world happy. Huh?\NYou cannot make these people happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.31,0:02:39.04,Default,,0,0,0,,You cannot live and hate etc. and be\Nhappy. Okay? So for the sake of your own
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.04,0:02:44.16,Default,,0,0,0,,happiness and but because as you as your\Nlevel of consciousness rises, you see
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.16,0:02:49.28,Default,,0,0,0,,you're lifting the world. The only\Nchance of these people being happy is by
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.28,0:02:54.08,Default,,0,0,0,,you being happier.\NThat's the only thing you can do.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.08,0:02:58.87,Default,,0,0,0,,As you become enlightened and happy, you\Nradiate out an energy. And I've walked
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.87,0:03:03.59,Default,,0,0,0,,through dangerous places. I mean,\Ndangerous like I don't want to tell you
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.59,0:03:07.92,Default,,0,0,0,,with complete safety. And all the guys\Njust looked at me in amazement. A
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.92,0:03:13.51,Default,,0,0,0,,cutthroat gang with whips, knives, guns,\Nand chains. And here's this short little
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.51,0:03:21.04,Default,,0,0,0,,shrimp walking right through the middle\Nof them. And they all just went
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.04,0:03:27.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and I walked through absolutely\Nuntouched.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.20,0:03:32.87,Default,,0,0,0,,A 6'6 professional Natalie would never\Neven tackle this crowd. All them whips,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.87,0:03:36.95,Default,,0,0,0,,knives, guns, and malice and tattoo from\Nhead to tent and roaring their
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.95,0:03:41.84,Default,,0,0,0,,motorcycles and just waiting for a rough\Nsomething to start up. And I went right
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.84,0:03:49.92,Default,,0,0,0,,through all them.\NI thought they were great looking guys,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.92,0:03:54.15,Default,,0,0,0,,you know.\NRemind me my lifetime as a pirate. They
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.15,0:03:57.36,Default,,0,0,0,,were just my buddies on the ship, you\Nknow, cutthroats. Everybody was a
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.36,0:04:04.23,Default,,0,0,0,,cutthroat. I mean, what's wrong?\N[laughter]
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.23,0:04:09.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Now I've been in very unsafe places and\Nand and come out of it alive, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.51,0:04:13.92,Default,,0,0,0,,in San Pan outside of Shanghai and\Nvarious places where I should have been
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.92,0:04:19.35,Default,,0,0,0,,killed, robbed, and tattooed, but uh I\Nthey delivered me home and put me on the
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.35,0:04:25.44,Default,,0,0,0,,doorstep, you know. So,\Nokay. So, it's what you become and not
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.44,0:04:28.63,Default,,0,0,0,,what you do. All right, we'll move to\Nthe next.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.63,0:04:34.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I just put this in for fun.\NUh this is the Louve.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.47,0:04:38.56,Default,,0,0,0,,There's the Lou, which is 700 years old\Nor something. Uh, and in the middle of
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.56,0:04:46.72,Default,,0,0,0,,it is an abomination.\N[laughter]
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.72,0:04:52.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's this crystal and glass\Nabomination which calibrates at 180.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.96,0:04:56.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And I don't know if any of you remember\Nthe contention with with France and who
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.72,0:05:01.36,Default,,0,0,0,,was the premier of France at the time.\NAnyway, they think they were being very
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.36,0:05:07.52,Default,,0,0,0,,very modern. very very modern. Anyway,\Nit's of course a disgrace when 180. It's
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.52,0:05:10.24,Default,,0,0,0,,very functional. No doubt about it. I\Nmean, it's great. You walk in the
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.24,0:05:14.24,Default,,0,0,0,,basement and you go up to everything. Uh\Nit's just aesthetically in the middle of
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.24,0:05:18.33,Default,,0,0,0,,the Lou. I don't suppose I would have\Nput that there myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.33,0:05:21.36,Default,,0,0,0,,[laughter]\NChrome steel and glass in the middle of
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.36,0:05:27.28,Default,,0,0,0,,the feudal beauty. You know what I mean?\N[laughter]
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.28,0:05:31.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Brussels, you know, the main square in\NBrussels in cobblestone and around you
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.19,0:05:34.40,Default,,0,0,0,,are all these incredible feudal\Nbuildings. I don't know if any of you
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.40,0:05:39.12,Default,,0,0,0,,have been there, but it's worth a trip\Nto just to experience that. I said,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.12,0:05:43.68,Default,,0,0,0,,yeah, and to picture a modernistic\Nbuilding would be an abomination anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.68,0:05:51.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, we'll just move that in there. I\Nput that in for my own personal fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.44,0:05:54.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, we're going to talk about spiritual\Ntruth.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.88,0:05:58.47,Default,,0,0,0,,See, first we need a science of truth.\NThen we need to apply it to the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.47,0:06:01.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Truth versus falsehood, which was not\Neverybody's favorite book, and that's
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.44,0:06:06.40,Default,,0,0,0,,too bad\Nbecause man says he's interested in the
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.40,0:06:09.12,Default,,0,0,0,,truth, but he ain't. I mean, nothing\Nmakes him mad. Then you present it with
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.12,0:06:15.28,Default,,0,0,0,,the truth. Indignant. Indignant. How can\Nyou say? I didn't say. First of all, I
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.28,0:06:18.96,Default,,0,0,0,,didn't say, as you can see this morning,\Nwhen we do kinesiology, I don't say
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.96,0:06:24.08,Default,,0,0,0,,anything. She doesn't say anything. We\Njust come up with a number. What do we
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.08,0:06:29.75,Default,,0,0,0,,care? It's only just a number. Nobody's\Nsaying anything about anything. Then the
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.75,0:06:33.12,Default,,0,0,0,,number clues you into whether you're\Nreally delusional or you ought to look
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.12,0:06:42.80,Default,,0,0,0,,at this or pray for help or what call\Nyour therapists.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.80,0:06:47.91,Default,,0,0,0,,There are many false teachers in the uh\Nworld and I was myself quite amazed when
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.91,0:06:53.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I discovered how many there were. I mean\Nlots lots who are quite world famous
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.12,0:06:56.63,Default,,0,0,0,,also.\Nlots and they calibrated well at one
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.63,0:07:03.44,Default,,0,0,0,,time\Nand then crashed very often severely,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.44,0:07:08.96,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, not just coming down from 570\Nto 540 or something, but all the way
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.96,0:07:12.88,Default,,0,0,0,,down to 180 or something. And of course,\Na number of them have been on the
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.88,0:07:19.68,Default,,0,0,0,,internet of these recent times of the\Nscandals. So because you're putting the
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.68,0:07:24.16,Default,,0,0,0,,your eternal soul in the hands of a\Nteacher, you better know who that
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.16,0:07:27.59,Default,,0,0,0,,teacher is. I mean, I wouldn't be so\Ncareless. You really you're talking
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.59,0:07:31.68,Default,,0,0,0,,about your eternal soul, the karmic\Nperpetuation
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.68,0:07:35.91,Default,,0,0,0,,throughout all time.\NAnd you're going to put this in some
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.91,0:07:41.44,Default,,0,0,0,,flashy ad, go and get your orura read by\Nmaster so and so on. On the other side,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.44,0:07:45.71,Default,,0,0,0,,uh, of course, you have turned over all\Nall your property to
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.71,0:07:49.75,Default,,0,0,0,,[laughter]\NYou get a reading from master so and so
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.75,0:07:54.31,Default,,0,0,0,,through him on the other side only cost\Nyou 5,000 for your granddaughter except
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.31,0:07:59.59,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't have a granddaughter\Nthat was in the internet a local one
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.59,0:08:05.52,Default,,0,0,0,,local guru for five grand a guy reading\Non a non-existent felicia is yeah all
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.52,0:08:11.75,Default,,0,0,0,,right\Nso I want everybody that I I'm a teacher
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.75,0:08:18.08,Default,,0,0,0,,of I want to be responsible you know to\Ntell them the downside. Apparently these
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.08,0:08:21.52,Default,,0,0,0,,gurus fell because nobody their\Ninstructors did not instruct them of the
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.52,0:08:25.91,Default,,0,0,0,,downside. So in our lectures we\Nconstantly go over what is the downside
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.91,0:08:29.84,Default,,0,0,0,,of each level of consciousness. Where is\Nthe trap?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.84,0:08:33.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Um people say I'm beyond that. You're\Nnot beyond that at all. The Buddha at
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.68,0:08:37.91,Default,,0,0,0,,the last from 850 and up is very\Ndifficult. And the Buddha acknowledged
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.91,0:08:41.44,Default,,0,0,0,,it. He said I felt like my bones are\Nbeing broken because the demons are
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.44,0:08:47.83,Default,,0,0,0,,looking for erony weakness uh in your\Npsyche.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.83,0:08:51.92,Default,,0,0,0,,There are characteristics of spiritual\Ntruth that will carry you through if you
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.92,0:08:55.68,Default,,0,0,0,,know them. You don't need a list of who\Nthey are and what they calibrate. That's
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.68,0:08:59.04,Default,,0,0,0,,very handy. But if you know certain\Nbasics, it's more important to
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.04,0:09:04.56,Default,,0,0,0,,understand the basics. Truth is true at\Nall times and places independent of the
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.56,0:09:11.44,Default,,0,0,0,,culture, personalities or circumstances.\NTruth is always true no matter what. So
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.44,0:09:17.60,Default,,0,0,0,,if we calibrate\Nthe
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.60,0:09:25.68,Default,,0,0,0,,cathedral. It's Shark Cathe Cathedral.\NIt it it is that calibration is so no
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.68,0:09:30.56,Default,,0,0,0,,matter what truth is true at all times\Nand places,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.56,0:09:35.76,Default,,0,0,0,,non-exclusionary.\NIt's all inclusive, nonsecritive, and
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.76,0:09:41.68,Default,,0,0,0,,non sectarian.\NNobody owns truth. What?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.68,0:09:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,>> What?\N>> It's 12:30. You're lying to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.00,0:09:57.68,Default,,0,0,0,,She said, "It's 12:30 and I have to\Nstop."
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.68,0:10:03.44,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Okay, get one more. Not an exclusive.\NIt's It's not secret. Okay, thanks. Oh,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.44,0:10:07.04,Default,,0,0,0,,stop there.\N>> [applause]
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.04,0:10:12.80,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Now, uh, what time is left?\N>> Be back at 2:00.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.80,0:10:21.12,Default,,0,0,0,,>> You have to be back at 2:00 or else\Nor else you'll be late.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.12,0:10:32.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It's bad to be late.\N>> What number side are we up to?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.88,0:10:34.39,Default,,0,0,0,,>> 40.\N>> Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.39,0:10:44.07,Default,,0,0,0,,>> 40.\N>> 40. 40. Oh my god. We better move along.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.07,0:10:52.95,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Okay, we'll go back to where we were.\N>> Oh, 39.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.95,0:10:56.16,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Okay, so if you have the basic\Nprinciples,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.16,0:11:03.76,Default,,0,0,0,,uh you won't fall into the soup. And uh\Nso we're giving the basics of uh
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.76,0:11:09.20,Default,,0,0,0,,integrity of teachers and teaches\N[laughter]
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.20,0:11:13.83,Default,,0,0,0,,and as you as yourself evolves in\Nconsciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.83,0:11:18.95,Default,,0,0,0,,there are certain traps each level has\Nits trap and uh with forewarning you
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.95,0:11:23.36,Default,,0,0,0,,won't fall into it. A group like this,\Nyour biggest uh one of the biggest traps
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.36,0:11:28.24,Default,,0,0,0,,coming up is unconditional love and\Nlove. As you reach the energy of love,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.24,0:11:32.72,Default,,0,0,0,,you become quite attractive to other\Npeople and they will interpret it as
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.72,0:11:36.95,Default,,0,0,0,,personal love. People will fall in love\Nwith you all over the place. There was a
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.95,0:11:41.51,Default,,0,0,0,,period of time when I got propositioned\Na couple times a day.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.51,0:11:45.20,Default,,0,0,0,,[laughter]\NAnd I didn't have a teacher to warn me,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.20,0:11:50.72,Default,,0,0,0,,but I just\NI mean I knew the integrity of it was up
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.72,0:11:56.39,Default,,0,0,0,,up for you know being tested. So I\Nintuited it. But uh many fall for that
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.39,0:12:01.92,Default,,0,0,0,,one there. And uh then glamour the\Nglamour and uh we were we weren't
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.92,0:12:06.16,Default,,0,0,0,,allowed to use the title guru in the\Nbook. Every time we'd ask it said no.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.16,0:12:10.63,Default,,0,0,0,,The word word has come to mean something\Ndifferent than what it what originally
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.63,0:12:18.07,Default,,0,0,0,,meant because it was being exploited.\NUh wealth, fame, having lots of
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.07,0:12:22.07,Default,,0,0,0,,followers,\Nuh
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.07,0:12:27.20,Default,,0,0,0,,having millions of followers across the\Nglobe, etc., world fame. So all those
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.20,0:12:32.24,Default,,0,0,0,,things are temptations to the spiritual\Nego to consider yourself important. And
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.24,0:12:36.95,Default,,0,0,0,,you see how the the spiritual ego throws\Nyou right back into a personal self
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.95,0:12:43.20,Default,,0,0,0,,right away. So the minute you think it's\Nyou, you just lost it. [laughter]
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.20,0:12:50.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It was it was but it was not not\Nanymore. Uh so spiritual pride
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.24,0:12:55.83,Default,,0,0,0,,uh vanity\Nuh the agilation of many followers
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.83,0:13:01.60,Default,,0,0,0,,being world famous all those things and\Nseduction and glamour of wealth and fame
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.60,0:13:08.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and possessions. Yeah.\NAnd uh the glamorization of the the
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.48,0:13:14.07,Default,,0,0,0,,glamorization of the spiritual teacher\Nwith robes and music and edififices and
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.07,0:13:21.51,Default,,0,0,0,,pageantry and parades and all that uh is\Nuh seduction.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.51,0:13:25.60,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. So we were talking about\Nspiritual truth and teachers.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.60,0:13:31.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh truth is true everywhere. It excludes\Nno one. Available
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.44,0:13:38.88,Default,,0,0,0,,open to all. There are no secrets to be\Nrevealed, hidden, sold or magical
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.88,0:13:43.60,Default,,0,0,0,,formulas or mysteries. Let me just\Nconfirm
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.60,0:13:49.36,Default,,0,0,0,,that which I spoke is the truth. Oh\NLord, resist that is the truth. When you
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.36,0:13:54.07,Default,,0,0,0,,see a secret, an ancient secret being\Npedal is always for a price, you know
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.07,0:13:57.75,Default,,0,0,0,,that you're being had by a spiritual\Ncomment.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.75,0:14:03.12,Default,,0,0,0,,[laughter]\NTruth to be truth is truth all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.12,0:14:09.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Foreverness. And how could it be the\Nexclusive property of someone? Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.27,0:14:14.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh available. It's open to all.\N[clears throat] Integrity of purpose.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.24,0:14:18.72,Default,,0,0,0,,There's nothing to gain or lose. Non\Nsectarian.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.72,0:14:23.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Truth is not the exposition of a\Nlimitation. Independent of opinion.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.60,0:14:29.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Truth is nonlinear. Therefore, not\Nsubject to limitations of intellect or
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.76,0:14:36.56,Default,,0,0,0,,form. independent of opinion, devoid of\Npositionality. Truth is not anti-
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.56,0:14:42.16,Default,,0,0,0,,anything. Why is that? Because truth has\Nno opposite.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.16,0:14:47.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It only has it. The you might say the\Nopposite of truth is is absence.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.92,0:14:51.83,Default,,0,0,0,,You understand what I'm saying? The\Nfalsehood has no reality. There's truth
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.83,0:14:55.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and then there's the absence of truth.\NThe absence of truth. So there's only
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.60,0:15:01.12,Default,,0,0,0,,truth and the absence. And we call the\Nabsence of truth falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.12,0:15:05.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Uhhuh.\NJust like light and darkness. See, light
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.12,0:15:11.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and darkness. Light is either present or\Nnot present. Yeah. No requirements or
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.60,0:15:16.32,Default,,0,0,0,,demands. No required memberships, dues,\Nfees, regulations, oaths, rules,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.32,0:15:22.39,Default,,0,0,0,,conditions, and we don't uh circul\Ncircularize everybody asking for
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.39,0:15:30.24,Default,,0,0,0,,donations. [laughter]\NNon-controlling spiritual purity has no
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.24,0:15:35.44,Default,,0,0,0,,interest in the personal lives of the\Naspirants in their clothing, their
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.44,0:15:40.16,Default,,0,0,0,,dress, their style, their sex life,\Ntheir economics, their family patterns,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.16,0:15:46.88,Default,,0,0,0,,their lifestyle or their dietary habits.\NSo the controlling pseudo guru, you
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.88,0:15:51.12,Default,,0,0,0,,know, is always telling you have to have\Nhis approval to get married. You have to
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.12,0:15:55.04,Default,,0,0,0,,etc.\NAnd of course,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.04,0:15:59.68,Default,,0,0,0,,sign over your wealth and your ownings,\Nyour possessions to them. [laughter]
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.68,0:16:05.83,Default,,0,0,0,,That's an important part.\NAnd some are local. There's some local
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.83,0:16:11.44,Default,,0,0,0,,people here who violate every single\Nsentence. Every single sentence. Every
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.44,0:16:16.07,Default,,0,0,0,,single sentence. They want to control\Nyour lifestyle. Now, why would anybody
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.07,0:16:20.48,Default,,0,0,0,,who was interested in an infinite truth\Nbe interested in your sex life, your
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.48,0:16:23.83,Default,,0,0,0,,dress life, your or what the hell you do\Nwith your personal life? I mean, why
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.83,0:16:27.44,Default,,0,0,0,,would he be interested in it except\Nthere's something in it for him? You
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.44,0:16:31.44,Default,,0,0,0,,know, control.\NSo, you would have no interest in that
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.44,0:16:36.80,Default,,0,0,0,,which is linear and personal and\Nobviously karmic etc. What would you
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.80,0:16:41.36,Default,,0,0,0,,care about such things? Free of force or\Nintimidation. We, you know, people are
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.36,0:16:44.95,Default,,0,0,0,,threatened. There are spiritual groups\Nincluding locally where you belong to
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.95,0:16:50.16,Default,,0,0,0,,the sect and if you try to get out of it\Nthere are uh recriminations
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.16,0:16:55.83,Default,,0,0,0,,sometimes quite severe\Nuh no force or intimidation there's no
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.83,0:16:59.92,Default,,0,0,0,,brainwashing\Nagilation of the leaders no training
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.92,0:17:04.88,Default,,0,0,0,,rituals watch out for training rituals\Nthat's a call the brainwash indoctrin by
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.88,0:17:10.07,Default,,0,0,0,,which you're indoctrinated\Nindoctrination anything called the
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.07,0:17:16.88,Default,,0,0,0,,training watch\Ntraining.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.88,0:17:20.72,Default,,0,0,0,,If you know the truth, what do you need\Nto be trained?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.72,0:17:25.67,Default,,0,0,0,,People a relic occasionally has one on\Nthis program. There's a guy from I think
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.67,0:17:29.67,Default,,0,0,0,,it's the Islamic world or what and he\Ngets on you can you can tell
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.67,0:17:33.12,Default,,0,0,0,,brainwashing it has a sound and a sight\Nto it. You can tell the instant you hear
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.12,0:17:38.72,Default,,0,0,0,,it. It's almost like a mechanicalness\Nand and he's like reciting a program
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.72,0:17:42.55,Default,,0,0,0,,that he's been programmed with. Once I\Ntell you that, you'll you'll pick up
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.55,0:17:47.28,Default,,0,0,0,,programming instantly. They have a\Ncertain style and a mechanicalness to
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.28,0:17:50.88,Default,,0,0,0,,their dissertation. And you can hear\Nit's a whole program that they're
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.88,0:17:58.79,Default,,0,0,0,,reading out of their poor poor mind.\NAll right. What's next? Uh any more to
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.79,0:18:05.44,Default,,0,0,0,,this? Oh, nonbinding.\NDo not take any oaths.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.44,0:18:11.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Do not pledge anything.\NAnd if I fail to break these vows, may
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.12,0:18:15.76,Default,,0,0,0,,such and such happen to me. Never take\Nsuch a vow. It'll cost you lifetimes
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.76,0:18:26.96,Default,,0,0,0,,later.\NI know.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.96,0:18:31.60,Default,,0,0,0,,See, you forgot that in life, that\Nlifetime, you made that commitment and
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.60,0:18:37.36,Default,,0,0,0,,swore to it by blood, etc. You've\Nforgotten that, but it's still you're
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.36,0:18:43.20,Default,,0,0,0,,still held to it. Just all right.\NNon-binding freedom. Free to come and go
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.20,0:18:47.76,Default,,0,0,0,,without persuasion, coercion,\Nintimidation, or consequences. There's
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.76,0:18:52.48,Default,,0,0,0,,no hierarchy. Instead, there is\Nvoluntary fulfillment of practical
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.48,0:18:56.16,Default,,0,0,0,,necessities and duties. Everybody we\Nwork with does what they go do because
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.16,0:19:05.91,Default,,0,0,0,,that's what needs to be done. [laughter]\NCommonality
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.91,0:19:11.20,Default,,0,0,0,,ah recognition. Let's say if you do have\Na leader or people who that you honor,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.20,0:19:17.44,Default,,0,0,0,,it's because of what one has become\Nrather than as a result of some title
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.44,0:19:23.91,Default,,0,0,0,,or trapping the great Baham you know you\Nknow bam because he's the great Baham
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.91,0:19:27.36,Default,,0,0,0,,you know what do you mean he's the great\NBaham who said he's the great Baham he
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.36,0:19:34.32,Default,,0,0,0,,say he's the great bah oh\Nyou recognize truth when you see it and
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.32,0:19:38.79,Default,,0,0,0,,so I respect all that exists because of\Nthe essence of that which they are,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.79,0:19:43.67,Default,,0,0,0,,which I sense right away. Therefore, you\Ngive respect to the the little beetle
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.67,0:19:47.91,Default,,0,0,0,,walking along. You give respect to the\Nanimals. You give respect to the polar
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.91,0:19:53.76,Default,,0,0,0,,bear. You give respect to all that\Nexists by virtue of that which it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.76,0:19:59.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh. Mhm.\NThe essence of the thing is that which
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.28,0:20:06.24,Default,,0,0,0,,it is, you know. And what does a thing\Nmean? What a thing means is what it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.24,0:20:13.03,Default,,0,0,0,,What it is is what it means.\NThat's hard to see, but then you get the
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.03,0:20:19.44,Default,,0,0,0,,essence of it. You see, what this thing\Nmeans is what it is. You don't have to
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.44,0:20:23.67,Default,,0,0,0,,add adjectives, adverbs,\Nlanguaging.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.67,0:20:29.52,Default,,0,0,0,,It speaks for itself by virtue of its\Nexistence. So, a teacher should be will
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.52,0:20:34.32,Default,,0,0,0,,speak for himself because of the reality\Nof that which it is. That which it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.32,0:20:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\Nnot not that which is spoken about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.00,0:20:42.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. Nonmaterialistic\Nneediness of worldly wealth and all this
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.79,0:20:50.15,Default,,0,0,0,,stuff that goes with it. Uh\Nso
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.15,0:20:55.28,Default,,0,0,0,,inspirational truth avoids\Nglamorization, seduction and theatrics.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.28,0:21:01.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Theatrics the glamorization of the\Ntheatrics. And I've been to so-called
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.60,0:21:05.28,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritual events that were like a\NBroadway production, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.28,0:21:10.55,Default,,0,0,0,,3D videos and bombing music and\Norchestras and flashing lights and holy
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.55,0:21:14.55,Default,,0,0,0,,god you know\Nam I being programmed or I mean what is
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.55,0:21:21.84,Default,,0,0,0,,this\Nyou no need for worldly wealth you see
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.84,0:21:27.08,Default,,0,0,0,,today's uh this week's what is it time\Nmagazine I think
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.08,0:21:33.91,Default,,0,0,0,,[clears throat] Frank cover has an issue\Non the religious argument about wealth
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.91,0:21:39.36,Default,,0,0,0,,isn't that Time magazine has it been?\NYeah. Uh wealth etc. And the
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.36,0:21:44.40,Default,,0,0,0,,promulgation of the idea that God's will\Nfor us is abundance. And then of course
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.40,0:21:50.15,Default,,0,0,0,,there's an ancient one of uh poverty.\NAnd so what is the truth? Does God mean
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.15,0:21:55.20,Default,,0,0,0,,for you to have lots of stuff or no\Nstuff or hardly any stuff or just a
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.20,0:22:01.03,Default,,0,0,0,,little stuff? [laughter]\NSo there's evangelicals out there
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.03,0:22:04.32,Default,,0,0,0,,telling you God's will for you is\Nabundance. I'm all for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.32,0:22:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And then there's people saying out\Nthere, you don't need anything. Uh and
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.00,0:22:15.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's better to be devoid of\Npossessions. And I'm all for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.03,0:22:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Best thing to do is be completely\Npovertystricken and have a lot of money.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.00,0:22:29.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it's because they don't define\Nwhat is wealth.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.84,0:22:33.84,Default,,0,0,0,,See wealth is a is the difference\Nbetween your desires and that which you
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.84,0:22:38.08,Default,,0,0,0,,have. So when you don't want anything\Nnow wantingness is one of the greatest
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.08,0:22:42.24,Default,,0,0,0,,things if you want to transcend quickly\Nto let go of wantingness. Letting
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.24,0:22:47.44,Default,,0,0,0,,wanting this wanting admiration wanting\Npossessions wanting control wanting all
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.44,0:22:51.20,Default,,0,0,0,,the wantingness. When you finally let go\Nall the wantingness you've got more than
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.20,0:22:57.03,Default,,0,0,0,,what you need.\NYou get more than what you need. When I
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.03,0:23:00.88,Default,,0,0,0,,first came to Sedona, I lived in a ready\Nplace. I didn't have a bed, so I went
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.88,0:23:05.91,Default,,0,0,0,,and bought a cot at the darn store. I\Nbought some blankets at the Goodwill.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.91,0:23:12.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I got a nice wooden box\Nand put a candlestick next to it. And I
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.08,0:23:17.52,Default,,0,0,0,,was complete. What What more do you\Nneed? [laughter]
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.52,0:23:24.79,Default,,0,0,0,,And uh I put an apple in the\Nrefrigerator and save that for dinner.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.79,0:23:29.67,Default,,0,0,0,,So what more do you need?\N>> Life space. You got nutrition when you
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.67,0:23:34.55,Default,,0,0,0,,want it. And of course, God will provide\Nfor you if you need. So I tested that
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.55,0:23:38.08,Default,,0,0,0,,out, too. Of course, a miracle said\Nthat. So I walked out with no money or
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.08,0:23:41.84,Default,,0,0,0,,no food and wandered around Sedona. I\Ngot invited for breakfast. I got invited
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.84,0:23:45.52,Default,,0,0,0,,for lunch and invited for dinner.\N[laughter]
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.52,0:23:48.15,Default,,0,0,0,,People would just say, "Do you have\Nbreakfast yet?" "No, I'm going over to
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.15,0:23:51.52,Default,,0,0,0,,so and so." I said, "I haven't got any\Nmoney. It's not It's not the house."
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.52,0:23:56.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So anyway, um, what you need is\Nprovided. Therefore, if you need
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.40,0:24:01.36,Default,,0,0,0,,nothing, you already have abundance. You\Nunderstand? I already have abundance.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.36,0:24:06.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Why am I going to seek abundance when\NI've got tons of abundance? Can I live
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.08,0:24:10.88,Default,,0,0,0,,without a sport jacket? Yeah. I mean, do\NI need all this stuff? Frankly, no. I
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.88,0:24:15.42,Default,,0,0,0,,need a pair of shoes, pair of pants,\Nshirt. So, what else do you need?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.42,0:24:25.12,Default,,0,0,0,,[laughter]\NI am rich and fulfilled and complete as
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.12,0:24:32.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I stand here now. That which I am right\Nnow is complete and total and needs
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.40,0:24:37.67,Default,,0,0,0,,nothing.\N[clears throat] That is a statement of
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.67,0:24:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the truth.\NAs I stand here, I am complete and total
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.00,0:24:54.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and need nothing.\N>> What more could you add to me that would
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.08,0:25:08.40,Default,,0,0,0,,not become a burden?\N>> She's giving away my secret.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.40,0:25:15.36,Default,,0,0,0,,She comes from an old-fashioned middle\Nclass value system
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.36,0:25:22.24,Default,,0,0,0,,that says if a thing is raggy and worn\Nout, you should throw it away. And I
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.24,0:25:25.67,Default,,0,0,0,,my favorite shirts and clothes at home\Nare all raggy and worn out, and I love
Dialogue: 0,0:25:25.67,0:25:30.15,Default,,0,0,0,,them.\NBut it has a hole in the elbow. Well, so
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.15,0:25:34.88,Default,,0,0,0,,what?\NRaggy old clothes. There was the the the
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.88,0:25:40.79,Default,,0,0,0,,the black doctor who who did all the\Nwork with peanuts. It was a very
Dialogue: 0,0:25:40.79,0:25:45.91,Default,,0,0,0,,wonderful all kinds of inventions.\N>> Carver. Carver. Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.91,0:25:50.64,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Well, he was a comp\Nlike I am. He he wore raggedy old
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.64,0:25:54.32,Default,,0,0,0,,clothes and that was his favorite. So,\Nif you have a new shirt and an old
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.32,0:25:58.55,Default,,0,0,0,,raggedy shirt, I always take the old\Nraggedy shirt. I don't know what it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.55,0:26:02.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So therefore,\Num,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.48,0:26:07.12,Default,,0,0,0,,you have wealth. It's just you don't\Nrealize it. And almost all Americans
Dialogue: 0,0:26:07.12,0:26:11.67,Default,,0,0,0,,have more than they need despite\Nwhatever they may think about it. Uh
Dialogue: 0,0:26:11.67,0:26:14.48,Default,,0,0,0,,because if you don't have any money, you\Ncan go someplace where they give out
Dialogue: 0,0:26:14.48,0:26:17.60,Default,,0,0,0,,free food for those that are homeless\Nand have no money. So again, you got
Dialogue: 0,0:26:17.60,0:26:22.32,Default,,0,0,0,,abundance, right?\NUh [clears throat]
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.32,0:26:27.44,Default,,0,0,0,,so the recognition is that what you\Nbecome, not your trappings. Uh the
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.44,0:26:31.67,Default,,0,0,0,,teacher should be inspirational rather\Nthan depending on seduction and
Dialogue: 0,0:26:31.67,0:26:39.12,Default,,0,0,0,,theatrics and um\Ndevoid of worldly affairs and uh the
Dialogue: 0,0:26:39.12,0:26:43.67,Default,,0,0,0,,these things are okay if they're part of\Nwhat the world demands that you have.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:43.67,0:26:47.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure there are spiritual positions\Nand religious ones where you more or
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.60,0:26:54.32,Default,,0,0,0,,less got to have whatever goes with it\Nbecause that's the cultural expectation.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:54.32,0:27:00.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh you don't have to sign up anybody\Nprosize gain followers sign up members
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.08,0:27:04.88,Default,,0,0,0,,non-involvement in world affairs truth\Nis benign
Dialogue: 0,0:27:04.88,0:27:11.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and has no opposites and therefore no\Nenemies and no enemies non-intentional
Dialogue: 0,0:27:11.36,0:27:17.52,Default,,0,0,0,,does not have an agenda does not wish to\Npromulgate anything does not interfere
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.52,0:27:22.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and try to change the world\Nnon-dualistic all transpires by virtue
Dialogue: 0,0:27:22.96,0:27:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,of the propensity\Nwithin the field by which potentiality
Dialogue: 0,0:27:28.00,0:27:35.03,Default,,0,0,0,,manifests as actuality\Nrather than by cause and effect. All
Dialogue: 0,0:27:35.03,0:27:41.12,Default,,0,0,0,,right, we've already said that. Okay.\NSo, there's no way to make things happen
Dialogue: 0,0:27:41.12,0:27:47.76,Default,,0,0,0,,by magic potions. Magic potions and\Nmagic spells and incantations and magic
Dialogue: 0,0:27:47.76,0:27:53.76,Default,,0,0,0,,ruins and marbles and magic toebones\Nthrowing the toebones. You know what I
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.76,0:28:00.15,Default,,0,0,0,,mean? [laughter]\NTranquility. There are no issues of
Dialogue: 0,0:28:00.15,0:28:04.55,Default,,0,0,0,,partialism.\NNot dependent on propagation of effort.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:04.55,0:28:10.32,Default,,0,0,0,,God doesn't need help other than any\Nmore than gravity needs the help of of
Dialogue: 0,0:28:10.32,0:28:15.60,Default,,0,0,0,,an apple falling off the tree.\NYeah. Here to help God. That's a very
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.60,0:28:21.12,Default,,0,0,0,,nice intention. But God doesn't really\Nneed help. [laughter]
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.12,0:28:25.76,Default,,0,0,0,,If you want to change the world, you\Nfeel that God needs help. And uh, of
Dialogue: 0,0:28:25.76,0:28:30.87,Default,,0,0,0,,course, you can convert people easily by\Ncutting their heads off if they don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.87,0:28:34.24,Default,,0,0,0,,[laughter]\NExcept the folks say that don't count.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.24,0:28:37.60,Default,,0,0,0,,So I don't know what you can say about\Nthat.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:37.60,0:28:43.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So So God doesn't need help. All right.\NEquality expressed in reverence for all
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.44,0:28:48.32,Default,,0,0,0,,of life and all of its expressions and\Navoids that which is dilitterious rather
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.32,0:28:53.27,Default,,0,0,0,,than opposing it. So you don't have an\Nenemy. Uh you just refuse it. And I
Dialogue: 0,0:28:53.27,0:28:57.44,Default,,0,0,0,,think that's what Jesus Christ\Nrecommended. Do not oppose evil. Avoid
Dialogue: 0,0:28:57.44,0:29:02.79,Default,,0,0,0,,it. Withdraw from it. Uh rather than\Ndoing battle with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.79,0:29:08.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Beyond proof that which is provable is\Nlinear, limited and a product of
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.32,0:29:13.44,Default,,0,0,0,,intellectualization and mentation. It's\Nwithin the linear domain.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.44,0:29:19.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Reality needs no agreement. Reality is\Nnot an acquisition and is spontaneous
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.52,0:29:25.84,Default,,0,0,0,,because it is nonlinear.\NMystical. The origination of truth is a
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.84,0:29:31.20,Default,,0,0,0,,spontaneous eulgence, a radiance and\Nillumination which is the revelation
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.20,0:29:35.76,Default,,0,0,0,,that replaces the illusion of separate\Nindividual self the ego and its
